name: PayingParty
label: paying party
definition: party responsible for making payments in a transaction specified in a contract

name: DerivativeSettlementTerms
label: derivative settlement terms
definition: settlement terms specifying additional details with respect to what is to be delivered when, to whom, under what conditions at the time of settlement

name: DerivativeTerms
definition: contractual terms specific to derivative contracts, including terms related to payments and delivery between parties
label: derivative terms

name: UniqueProductIdentifier
definition: sequence of characters uniquely identifying an OTC derivative product that is reportable to a trade repository
label: unique product identifier
explanatoryNote:
The UPI code consists of 12 alphanumeric characters decomposed as follows:
		- the two-character prefix 'QZ'
		- nine alphanumeric characters (upper case A-Z and 0-9 only, excluding the vowel characters (A, E, I, O, U) and the character Y) without separators or special characters
		- one alphanumeric check character (A-Z and 0-9 only, excluding the vowel characters (A, E, I, O, U) and the character Y), calculated using the method specified in Annex C of the specification document.

name: OverTheCounterDerivativeInstrument
definition: derivative instrument that is not listed on an organized exchange
label: over-the-counter derivative instrument

name: OverTheCounterInstrument
label: over-the-counter instrument
definition: financial instrument and bilateral contract that is not listed on an organized exchange

name: UniqueProductIdentifierRegistryEntry
explanatoryNote: The Reference Data Library (RDL) is a set of reference data elements, together with their values, which is properly organized and maintained by the UPI service provider. The library associates UPI codes with the values of the reference data elements characterizing the product. Each entry in the library (the registry entry) contains a minimum number of elements as defined in the ISO standard, and may be extended by the service provider.
definition: entry in a unique product identifier registry
label: unique product identifier registry entry

name: ReceivingParty
label: receiving counterparty
definition: party that receives payments in a transaction specified in a contract

name: UniqueProductIdentifierServiceProvider
definition: organization designated by an external body of financial regulators to assign UPIs and operate a UPI reference data library
label: unique product identifier service provider

name: CreditDerivative
explanatoryNote: The third party accepts the risk in return for payment, known as the premium.
label: credit derivative
definition: derivative instrument that is a privately held, negotiable bilateral contract traded over-the-counter (OTC) between two parties in a creditor/debtor relationship, enabling the creditor to effectively transfer some or all of the risk of a debtor defaulting to a third party

name: IntroducingBroker
label: introducing broker
explanatoryNote: Introducing brokers do not accept money, securities, or property (or extend credit in lieu thereof) to margin, guarantee, or secure any trades or contracts that result or may result.
definition: broker that solicits or accepts orders for derivatives that are traded on or subject to the rules of an exchange

name: CashflowExpression
definition: expression that specifies a calculation of a cash flow as a component of a cashflow formula
label: cashflow expression

name: CalculationAgent
explanatoryNote: The calculation agent can also establish the price for a structured product and may act as its guarantor and issuer. If the counterparty in a derivative transaction is a broker-dealer, then they will often act as the calculation agent.
label: calculation agent
definition: party that is responsible for determining the value of a derivative and in some cases, determines how much the parties owe one another

name: CashflowFormula
definition: formula for determining cashflows for a derivative instrument
label: cashflow formula

name: ValuationTerms
definition: contract terms specific to valuation of the underlying asset(s)
label: valuation terms

name: ContractForDifference
explanatoryNote: These contracts can also be on the difference of two assets' prices. They can also be on the difference of a single asset of different maturities (like a bond or futures contracts).
definition: cash-settled derivative where the parties agree to exchange on the maturity of the contract the difference between the current value of the underlying asset and the initial value of that asset when the contract is initiated
label: contract for difference

name: CashflowTerms
definition: terms setting out a cashflow structure of payments committed to by one party to a contract
label: cashflow terms

name: ObservableValue
label: observable value
definition: value for something discernible and for which evidence can be obtained
explanatoryNote: Derivatives, such as certain exotics, can be based on values ascribed to virtually anything, including weather. Typically, however, an observable value refers to something that can be readily observed in the marketplace, such as a quoted rate (e.g., interest rate, exchange rate), index value, commodity price, stock price, economic indicator, or something similar as of some point in time.

name: UnderlyingAssetValuation
definition: assessment activity to estimate the value of an underlying asset of a derivative
label: underlying asset valuation

name: DerivativesClearingOrganization
definition: clearing house that enables parties to substitute the credit of the DCO for the credit of the parties
explanatoryNote: Substitution may be done through contract novation, for example. A derivatives clearing organization (DCO) also arranges or provides, on a multilateral basis, for the settlement or netting of obligations, or otherwise provides clearing services or arrangements that mutualize or transfer credit risk among participants.
label: derivatives clearing organization

name: ParametricCashflowTerms
label: parametric cashflow terms
definition: terms for a set of cashflows defined according to a mathematical formula

name: hasFirstNoticeDate
definition: specifies the initial date on which a delivery notice can be issued
label: has first notice date

name: hasTickValue
definition: indicates the cash value of one tick, i.e., the minimum price change of the contract
label: has tick value

name: hasUnderlyingAssetPrice
label: has underlying asset price
definition: specifies a price for something on which the contract is based

name: UniqueProductIdentifierReferenceDataLibrary
label: unique product identifier reference data library
definition: set of data comprised of reference data elements with specific values that together describe the product

name: hasLastNoticeDate
definition: specifies the final date on which a delivery notice can be issued
label: has last notice date

name: hasAccretingNotionalAmount
definition: indicates that the notional amount increases through the life of the contract
label: has accreting notional amount

name: hasCalculationAgent
label: has calculation agent
definition: indicates the party that is responsible for determining the value of a derivative

name: hasFirstDeliveryDate
definition: specifies the initial date in a range of dates by which the underlying asset (or some portion thereof) must be delivered in order for the terms of the contract to be fulfilled
label: has first delivery date

name: hasAdditionalCosts
definition: indicates costs, such as up front costs, brokerage fees and the like, that must be paid on delivery
label: has additional costs

name: hasCustomNotionalAmount
label: has custom notional amount
definition: indicates that the notional amount is customized per a notional step schedule

name: hasSettlementTerms
label: has settlement terms
definition: relates a derivative to contractual terms specific to the settlement process

name: hasValuationTerms
label: has valuation terms
definition: relates a derivative to contractual terms specific to valuation of the underlying asset(s)

name: hasLastDeliveryDate
definition: specifies the final date in a range of dates by which the underlying asset (or some portion thereof) must be delivered in order for the terms of the contract to be fulfilled
label: has last delivery date

name: hasAmortizingNotionalAmount
definition: indicates that the notional amount decreases through the life of the contract
label: has amortizing notional amount

name: hasConstantNotionalAmount
label: has constant notional amount
definition: indicates that the notional amount is constant through the life of the contract
